  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT226-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">varaiviṭai āṟṟāḷ eṉak kavaṉṟa tōḻikkuk kiḻatti uraittatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told by HER to the confidante who was anxious she would
          not have the strength [to await] the time of marriage.</p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT226">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l>pūvoṭu puraiyuṅ kaṇṇum vēyeṉa</l>
          <l>viṟalvaṉap peytiya tōḷum piṟaiyeṉa</l>
          <l>matimayak kuṟūu nutalu naṉṟu</l>
          <l>nallamaṉ vāḻi tōḻi yalkalun</l>
          <l>tayaṅkutirai poruta tāḻai veṇpūk</l>
          <l>kurukeṉa malarum peruntuṟai</l>
          <l>virinīrc cērppaṉoṭu nakāa vūṅkē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Very good certainly, oh friend, [was]</l>
          <l>the forehead, which confuses the mind into saying “crescent moon”,</l>
          <l>and the shoulder, which has reached victorious beauty</l>
          <l>so that [it] says “bamboo”, and the eyes, which are like flowers</l>
          <l rend="indent">– before having laughed with the man from the coast of the broad</l>
          <l rend="indent2">water with great ghats, where the white flowers of the Tāḻai tree</l>
          <l rend="indent7">are blossoming so that it says “egrets”,</l>
          <l rend="indent4">while the glittering waves dash against [it] all through the night.</l>

        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
